Object Oriented Programming

In all the programs we have wrote till now, we have designed our programs around funtions i.e blocks of statements which manipulate
data. This is called procedure-oriented programming. There is another way to organizing your program which is to combine data and
functionality and wrap inside something called an object. This is called the object oriented programming paradigm. 

Classes and Objects are the two main aspects of object oriented programming. A class creates a new type where objects are instances of the class. Objects can store data using odinary variables that belong to the object. Variables that belong to an object 